138
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,479
- That's excellent.
- Any side effects?

139
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:29,689
In one trial, yes.

140
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:32,536
It was an aberration. All the tests
since then have been successful.

141
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:34,777
And in the trial that went wrong,
what happened?

142
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,446
What were the side effects?

143
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:38,948
Violence, aggression...

144
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:40,867
...and insanity.

145
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:43,786
- What do you recommend?
- That was only one test.

146
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:47,874
Except for Dr. Stromm,
our entire staff certifies the product...

147
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,960
- ...ready for human testing.
- Dr. Stromm?

148
00:11:52,295 --> 00:11:54,923
We need to take the whole line
back to formula.

149
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:59,636
- Back to formula?
- Dr. Osborn.

150
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,639
I'll be frank with you.

151
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:07,727
I never supported your program. We
have my predecessor to thank for that.

152
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:10,647
Norman, the general gave
the go-ahead to Quest Aerospace...

153
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,733
...to build a prototype
of their exoskeleton design.

154
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,654
- They test in two weeks.
- And if your performance enhancers...

155
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:22,242
...have not had a successful
human trial by that date...

156
00:12:22,492 --> 00:12:26,871
...I'm gonna pull your funding.
I'm going to give it to them.

157
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:30,333
Gentlemen. Ladies.

158
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:40,843
And the Lord said, "Let there be light."
And voila! There is light.

159
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,179
Forty soft, glowing watts of it.

160
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:47,433
Mm. Good boy. God will be thrilled.
Just don't fall on your ass.

161
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,937
Heh, heh. I'm already on my ass, May.

162
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:55,608
When the plant's senior electrician
is laid off after 35 years...

163
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:58,486
...what else would you call it?
I am on my ass.

164
00:12:58,695 --> 00:13:01,030
Hand me that dish.
The green one.

165
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:04,033
The corporation is downsizing
the people...

166
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,369
...and upsizing their profits.

167
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,706
Oh, Ben,
you'll get another job somewhere.

168
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:13,459
Yeah, well...
Well, let's look in the paper and see.

169
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:17,380
There are the want ads.
What do we got here?

170
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:19,173
Computer.

171
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:23,136
Computer salesman, computer engineer,
computer analyst.

172
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:27,056
My Lord, even the computers
need analysts these days.

173
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:32,645
May, I'm 68. I'm too old for computers,
and besides, I have a family to provide for.

174
00:13:32,854 --> 00:13:35,732
I love you. And Peter loves you.

175
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:39,235
You're the most responsible man
I've ever known.

176
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:42,739
We've been down-and-out before.
But somehow, we survive.

177
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:43,906
Yeah.

178
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:49,329
Oh. Hi, sweetie. You're just--
Just in time for dinner.

179
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:52,081
Hey. How you doing, buddy?
How was the field trip?

180
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:55,084
I don't feel well.
I'm gonna go to sleep.

181
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:57,754
- You won't have a bite?
- No thanks. Had a bite.

182
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,340
Did you get some pictures, Peter?

183
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:04,010
Uh-- I gotta crash. Everything's fine.

184
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:07,013
What's that all about?

185
